Package org.antkar.syn

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    SourceDescriptor
    Source code (input) descriptor.
    TokenStream
    Token stream interface.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayNode
    Array node.
    FileSourceDescriptor
    Source descriptor representing a File.
    ObjectNode
    Object node.
    ObjectNode.ObjectEntry
    Map entry, a key-value pair.
    StringSourceDescriptor
    Source descriptor representing an arbitrary String.
    SynNode
    Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) node.
    SynParser
    A parser for a particular grammar.
    SynResult
    The result returned by a SynParser.
    TerminalNode
    Terminal node - a node that does not contain child nodes.
    TextPos
    A position in an input text.
    TokenDescriptor
    Token descriptor.
    ValueNode
    A terminal node that has an associated value, like an identifier or an integer number.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    SynValueType
    The type of a value associated with a value node.
    TokenType
    Token type.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    SynAmbiguityException
    Thrown by SynParser if a grammar ambiguity is detected, but only if the parser is configured to fail on an ambiguity.
    SynException
    Common superclass for all SYN exception types.
    SynGrammarException
    Thrown if there is a semantical error in the grammar passed to a SynParser.
    SynLexicalException
    Signals an error in lexical analysis.
    SynSyntaxException
    Thrown to indicate a syntax error - a situation when the input does not match the grammar.
    SynTextException
    Text exception - an exception associated with a position in the input.
